Former Public Enterprises Minister Malusi Gigaba is continuing his testimony at the state capture commission this afternoon. JOHANNESBURG - Former Public Enterprises Minister Malusi Gigaba is expected to continue giving testimony at the State Capture Inquiry. The commission says he'll discuss Gupta-related evidence. READ: Gupta name-dropping made me uncomfortable: Gigaba Gigaba has been accused by several witnesses including his estranged wife Norma Mngoma of being close to the controversial family but he's refuted their statements, saying he was uncomfortable with his name being dropped by the Gupta's and their associates.